The paper focuses on a segmentation method for medical images, specifically for the rectum/sigmoid colon in gynecological brachytherapy. This falls under the domain of computer vision (cs.CV) and graphics (cs.GR) as it involves image processing and visualization. The use of a graph-based segmentation scheme also suggests a potential connection to machine learning (cs.LG) and multimedia (cs.MM) as these fields often utilize graph-based algorithms. Finally, the evaluation of the proposed method involves comparing manual segmentations, which could potentially involve information retrieval (cs.IR) techniques.
